HAI
Age and diagnostics group 3-12 month; Infants with clinical sings of CP or a risc of developing CP 
Purpose: Measurea each hand separately and both hands together 
Test activity: Self selected toys to be approved
Items: 12 unimanual and 5 bimanual items 
Type of the test: Criterion and normreferenced

Mini-AHA
Age and diagnostic group: 8-18 month; Children with clinical signs of unilateral CP 
Purpose: Measures affected hand as used together with the non-affected hand
Test activity: Self selected toys to be aproved 
Items: 20 items
Type of test: Criterion referenced 

